  271. (** [options_with_command_line_syntax options r] returns [options2] that behaves
  272.     like [options], but additionally pushes command line argument on [r] (quoted
  273.     by [Filename.quote] when necessary).
  274.     This is meant for ocaml{c,opt}p, which use this to forward most of their
  275.     arguments to ocaml{c,opt}. *)
  276. val options_with_command_line_syntax
  277.   : (string * Arg.spec * string) list
  278.   -> string list ref
  279.   -> (string * Arg.spec * string) list
